    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_a450333e-79ac-4aac-b3d2-c0a0242c9f2b" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can record or upload media as a comment to a submission. You can record media for any length of time, but shorter media recordings are recommended. If your media is longer than 15 minutes, you may want to consider recording and uploading using an external provider. Longer media recordings require more time to render and may be interrupted without a stable internet connection.</p>
<p>Canvas videos also support caption files. Once you record and save your video, learn how to <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-add-captions-to-new-or-uploaded-videos-in-the-Rich/ta-p/529" target="_blank">add captions to a video</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Notes:Â </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Safari browser does not support recording media. Please use Chrome or Firefox to record media comments.</li>
<li>Recorded media files are stored in the Uploaded Media folder of your User Files. Learn how to <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-view-my-user-files-as-a-student/ta-p/483" target="_blank">view your user files</a>.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_grades" data-step-uuid="46367aff-e55e-4df4-a5a8-96984a79f4b2">
